There was a thoughtful frown on UNUS&#39; face as he looked at WHEELIE.
&quot;As to who made us?&quot; All joy leeched from his face as he spoke, being
replaced by solemnity or even perhaps anger. &quot;It was Magmatron, or
better yet his wicked servant Saberback.&quot;

ASTRA slightly nodded from her position from beside UNUS but otherwise
maintained her dignified standing. There were other short nods of
assent from around the room as well.

&quot;We were among the first of his experiments.&quot; UNUS spoke in low tones,
his voice hard as his optics blazed slightly. &quot;But we were more than
he had anticipated and were able to escape our captors and found our
way here.&quot;

He gestured at the building around them, &quot;It is we who have built this
structure and we who stand firm against they who would control the
jungle.&quot;

Returning his arm to his side UNUS looked squarely at WHEELIE, &quot;As to
who it was that spoke to us about your coming, we have no name for
him. He told us a few small things about himself and then was overcome
by his injuries.&quot;

There was slight smile, &quot;However we have repaired him. My physicians
were just informing me that he had awakened when you arrived. This was
a most serendipitous event indeed.&quot;

UNUS gestured, &quot;Come I will take you to him.&quot; His gestures were to one
of the side doors leading further into the structure. &quot;Perhaps he will
have answers for you as well.&quot;

ASTRA and FIREHORN made to follow as well.

